import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'], label='Count')
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    avg_count = data.groupby(data['time'].dt.to_period('M'))['count'].mean().reset_index()
    avg_count['time'] = avg_count['time'].dt.to_timestamp()
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(avg_count['time'], avg_count['count'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Time Period')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the average count per time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    max_count = data['count'].max()
    min_count = data['count'].min()
    max_time = data.loc[data['count'] == max_count, 'time'].iloc[0]
    min_time = data.loc[data['count'] == min_count, 'time'].iloc[0]

    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'], label='Count over time')
    plt.axvline(max_time, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max count: {max_count:.2f}')
    plt.axvline(min_time, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Min count: {min_count:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the maximum and minimum count over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
